  <h4 class="heading"><a name="general" id="general">General Rules</a></h4>
  
  <ol>
    <li>You may not use the EWA to impersonate any real person or entity. (Fictional content explicitly described as such, i.e. RPF in the first-person, does not constitute impersonation.)</li>
    <li>You may not use the EWA to post another person's copyrighted material. Quotes from source canon and/or references to source canon or other fanworks do not constitute copyright infringement.</li>
    <li>You may not use the EWA for advertisement, spam or chain letters.</li>
    <li>You may not use the EWA to distribute any material including malicious or potentially harmful code.</li>
    <li>You may not use the EWA for harassment, including of other users. RPF does not inherently constitute harassment.</li>
    <li>User icons must be safe for work.</li>
    <li>You must be above the age of 13 to create an account on the EWA.</li>
</ol>
 
  <h4 class="heading"><a name="content" id="content">Content Rules</a></h4>
  
  <p>The following content is prohibited:</p>
  
 <ol>
   <li>Sexually explicit material of any kind.</li>
   <li>"Safe for work" fetish material.</li>
   <li>Romantic ("Shipping") material of underage content creators in a RPF (Real Person Fiction) setting, or otherwise not in regards to a pre-existing fictional canon.</li>
   <li>Romantic ("Shipping") material of underage characters or people with adults regardless of setting.</li>
   <li>Romantic ("Shipping") material between characters or people that are biologically related or related by adoption or marriage (i.e. step-siblings), regardless of setting.</li>
   <li>Material which has no meaningful content outside of bigotry, including, but not limited to:
     <ul>
       <li>Material where the entire central focus is bigotry, especially graphic hate crimes</li>
       <li>Material that reflects real-world incidents of bigotry</li>
       <li>Material which condones bigotry or hateful worldviews and/or ideologies</li>
       <li>Material which contains the use of hateful slurs towards minority groups</li>
       <li>Material which directs bigoted comments at any real person directly, outside the context of fiction</li>
     </ul>
  <li>Material which does not fall within the scope of the Archive, as per defined in the categories below:</li>
   <ul>
     <li>Content creators who make Minecraft-related video content for the Internet, including Twitch streamers and YouTubers, or are directly associated with those who do.</li>
     <li>Fictional roleplay servers and stories in which Minecraft is used as a medium for storytelling, without regard to how much of these stories are pre-planned or scripted.</li>
     <li>Podcasts, web series, and other material created by MCYT Content Creators, as defined above, even if they do not directly correlate to Minecraft or the fandom.</li>
     <li>Fan-created stories, universes and works without direct ties to pre-existing canons or content creators, such as "Penis SMP".</li>
     <li>Original work related to Minecraft, such as works based on a user's own SMP server.</li>
     <li>Crossover work between any of the above categories and out-of-scope media.</li>
   </ul>
 </ol>
  
  <p>EWA staff reserves the right to remove any other material we deem unfit to host on the Archive, if a consensus is reached after discussion with the content moderation team.</p>
